18 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 17-20-303 is amended to read as follows:
19 17-20-303. Application.
20 (a) Any person, firm, or corporation desiring to operate as a barber,
21 barber student, teacher manager instructor, teacher manager instructor
22 student, barbershop, barber corporation, or barber school or college shall
23 file an application for a certificate of registration on a form furnished by
24 the State Board of Barber Examiners and pay the application fee.
25 (b) Any person who desires to practice barbering in this state shall
26 file with the Director of the State Board of Barber Examiners a written
27 application, duly notarized, with certification of at least one thousand five
28 hundred (1,500) hours of barber training, together with:
29 (1) Two (2) identical passport-sized signed photographs; and
30 (2) A copy of his or her driver’s license or record of state or
31 federal identification card; and.
32 (3) A copy of his or her Social Security card.
33 (c) A barber applying for reciprocity who has an unrevoked and
34 unexpired license issued by the proper authorities of another state
35 certifying that he or she has completed a minimum of one thousand five
36 hundred (1,500) hours of training, may be issued a certificate of
