8 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 17-20-304(a), concerning examinations for a
9 certificate of registration to practice as a registered barber, is amended to
10 read as follows:
11 (a) An applicant for a certificate of registration to practice as a
12 registered barber who fails to pass a satisfactory examination conducted by
13 the State Board of Barber Examiners may apply for another examination at any
14 future meeting of the board shall pass an examination approved by the State
15 Board of Barber Examiners.
16
17 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 17-20-307(d)(1), concerning a personal
18 lifetime barber license, is amended to read as follows:
19 (d)(1) A barber who holds a current license in this state shall be
20 issued a personal lifetime license at eighty (80) years of age upon his or
21 her request.
22
