3 SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 17-20-406(a)(1), concerning teacher manager
4 instructor certification for barber schools, is amended to read as follows:
5 (a)(1) Application for examination for a teacher manager instructor
6 certificate shall be filed with the State Board of Barber Examiners on blank
7 forms prepared and furnished by the board and shall be accompanied by the fee
8 prescribed in § 17-20-409.
9
10 SECTION 7. Arkansas Code § 17-20-407(c), concerning course of study,
11 is amended to read as follows:
12 (c) Each barber college shall abide by the following guidelines:
13 (1) Conduct a course of study and training which shall consist
14 of not fewer than five hundred fifty (550) hours for students who are
15 licensed cosmetologists, and as to all other students not fewer than one
16 thousand five hundred (1,500) clock hours. The average daily schedule of each
17 student shall consist of the following:
18 (A) One and one-fourth (1¼) clock hours of theoretical
19 study in a classroom;
20 (B) One and one-fourth (1¼) clock hours of scientific
21 barber practice in a classroom other than general clinic; and
22 (C) Five (5) clock hours of general barber practice. Each
23 barber college shall average five (5) services per day per student;
24 (2) Teach no fewer than one-third (⅓) of its total enrollment
25 scientific barbering practice, theory, or general barber practice at one (1)
26 time;
27 (3)(2) Post a daily schedule of its course of study in its
28 general clinic where it can be easily read by all students; and
29 (4)(3) Require a maximum attendance in all subjects. A student
30 shall not be permitted to spend more than eight (8) hours in the college in
31 any one (1) day.
32
