3 SECTION 9. Arkansas Code § 17-20-420 is amended to read as follows:
4 17-20-420. Application for enrollment.
5 (a) A school of barbering shall not enroll or admit any student
6 thereto unless the student makes and files in duplicate a duly verified
7 application submits to the State Board of Barber Examiners:
8 (1) An application; and
9 (2) The fee prescribed for the administration of the student
10 application and student license.
11 (b) This The application required under subsection (a) of this section
12 shall be of such form and contain such matters as the State Board of Barber
13 Examiners board may prescribe.
14 (b) One (1) copy of the application shall be retained by the school
15 enrolling or admitting the student, and one (1) copy shall be filed by the
16 school with the board, along with the fee prescribed for the administration
17 of the student application and student license.
18
19 SECTION 10. Arkansas Code § 17-20-421(a)(3), concerning applications
20 for admission to a barber college or examination to receive a certificate of
21 registration as a registered barber, is amended to read as follows:
22 (3) The application for enrollment shall be accompanied with
23 identification of the applicant in the form of:
24 (A) A copy of his or her Social Security card;
25 (B) A driver's license or a state-issued or federally-
26 issued identification card; and
27 (C)(B) Two (2) passport-sized photographs of the applicant
28 with the name of the applicant on the back.
